### Configure Max Samples Stored for New Relic Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

These configurations set the maximum number of samples stored for various event types in the New Relic Node.js agent. They can be set via configuration items or environment variables. Ensure you have sufficient resources if increasing these limits.

```json
{
  "span_events": {
    "max_samples_stored": 30000
  }
}
```

```dotenv
NEW_RELIC_SPAN_EVENTS_MAX_SAMPLES_STORED=30000
```

```json
{
  "transaction_events": {
    "max_samples_stored": 30000
  }
}
```

```dotenv
NEW_RELIC_TRANSACTION_EVENTS_MAX_SAMPLES_STORED=30000
```

```json
{
  "custom_insights_events": {
    "max_samples_stored": 30000
  }
}
```

```dotenv
NEW_RELIC_CUSTOM_INSIGHTS_EVENTS_MAX_SAMPLES_STORED=30000
```

```json
{
  "error_collector": {
    "max_event_samples_stored": 50
  }
}
```

```dotenv
NEW_RELIC_ERROR_COLLECTOR_MAX_EVENT_SAMPLES_STORED=50
```

