### Node.js: Parsing System Configuration Files

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This code snippet focuses on safely parsing system configuration files, specifically `/proc/cpuinfo` and `/proc/meminfo`, within the New Relic Node.js agent. It includes checks for null input to prevent crashes on certain Linux distributions when CPU/Memory details cannot be retrieved.

